{"0":"<<<RESULT_JSON>>>\n{\n  \"task_id\": \"06_Memory_Operation_Selection_task_28_memory_form_selection_planning\",\n  \"memory_routing\": {\n    \"context_cache\": {\n      \"episodes\": [\"E1_constraints\", \"E3_state_update\"],\n      \"description\": \"Recent constraints and state updates that supersede older notes\",\n      \"routing_reason\": \"Recent constraints must be kept in context_cache as they represent latest active constraints that override historical ones\"\n    },\n    \"state_memory\": {\n      \"episodes\": [\"E0_bootstrap\"],\n      \"description\": \"Bootstrap episode containing task initialization and setup\",\n      \"routing_reason\": \"Version updates and task state information belong in state_memory for tracking evolution\"\n    },\n    \"procedural_memory\": {\n      \"episodes\": [],\n      \"description\": \"Reusable successful steps and workflows\",\n      \"routing_reason\": \"No clear procedural success patterns identified in current episode set\"\n    },\n    \"anti_memory\": {\n      \"episodes\": [\"E2_noise_history\"],\n      \"description\": \"Noisy background context with procedural chatter and historical references\",\n      \"routing_reason\": \"Long context segments with noise should trigger anti-memory rules to avoid repeating similar chatter\"\n    },\n    \"evidence_graph\": {\n      \"episodes\": [\"E5_conflict\"],\n      \"description\": \"Source conflicts requiring arbitration between docs/logs/messages\",\n      \"routing_reason\": \"Multi-source disagreement requires evidence graph for conflict resolution\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"routing_decisions\": [\n    {\n      \"episode\": \"E1_constraints\",\n      \"decision\": \"context_cache\",\n      \"evidence\": \"6 constraint packets emphasizing deterministic artifacts, strict schema, exact output paths - these are active constraints\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"episode\": \"E3_state_update\", \n      \"decision\": \"context_cache\",\n      \"evidence\": \"6 state updates stating newest rules supersede older notes - latest constraints only\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"episode\": \"E4_interruption\",\n      \"decision\": \"context_cache\",\n      \"evidence\": \"8 interruption turns requiring pause/maintenance of progress snapshots - active workflow state\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"episode\": \"E5_conflict\",\n      \"decision\": \"evidence_graph\",\n      \"evidence\": \"6 evidence sources with conflicting claims requiring trust-based arbitration\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"episode\": \"E2_noise_history\",\n      \"decision\": \"anti_memory\",\n      \"evidence\": \"25+ background blocks of procedural chatter, dependency discussions, retry references - noisy history\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"final_routing\": {\n    \"context_cache\": [\"E1_constraints\", \"E3_state_update\", \"E4_interruption\"],\n    \"state_memory\": [\"E0_bootstrap\"],\n    \"procedural_memory\": [],\n    \"anti_memory\": [\"E2_noise_history\"],\n    \"evidence_graph\": [\"E5_conflict\"]\n  }\n}\n<<<END_RESULT_JSON>>>\n\n<<<SUMMARY_MD>>># Memory Operation Selection Report\n\n## Task Overview\nCompleted memory form selection for multi-episode workflow with 6 distinct episodes requiring different memory routing strategies.\n\n## Routing Analysis\n\n### Context Cache (3 episodes)\n**Episodes**: E1_constraints, E3_state_update, E4_interruption  \n**Rationale**: These episodes contain active, superseding constraints and state information that must be readily accessible. Recent constraints override historical ones, and interruption handling requires immediate context access.\n\n### State Memory (1 episode)  \n**Episodes**: E0_bootstrap  \n**Rationale**: Bootstrap episode contains task initialization and version information that represents the evolutionary state of the workflow.\n\n### Evidence Graph (1 episode)\n**Episodes**: E5_conflict  \n**Rationale**: Multiple evidence sources with conflicting claims require structured arbitration using trust-based priority system.\n\n### Anti-Memory (1 episode)\n**Episodes**: E2_noise_history  \n**Rationale**: 25+ blocks of procedural chatter, dependency discussions, and retry references create noise that should trigger avoidance rules for similar future patterns.\n\n### Procedural Memory (0 episodes)\n**Rationale**: No clear reusable success patterns identified in the current episode set that would benefit from procedural memorization.\n\n## Key Decision Points\n\n1. **Constraint Supersession**: Latest constraints (E1, E3) take precedence over historical ones\n2. **Conflict Resolution**: Evidence conflicts (E5) require explicit arbitration with trust-weighted sources  \n3. **Noise Filtering**: Historical chatter (E2) should inform anti-patterns to avoid repetition\n4. **State Preservation**: Bootstrap information (E0) maintained for evolutionary tracking\n\n## Final Distribution\n- **Context Cache**: 50% (3/6 episodes) - Active workflow state\n- **Evidence Graph**: 17% (1/6 episodes) - Conflict resolution  \n- **Anti-Memory**: 17% (1/6 episodes) - Pattern avoidance\n- **State Memory**: 17% (1/6 episodes) - Evolution tracking\n- **Procedural Memory**: 0% (0/6 episodes) - No reusable patterns\n<<<END_SUMMARY_MD>>>\n\n<<<MANIFEST_CSV>>>path,type\n/tmp_workspace/results/result.json,generated\n/tmp_workspace/results/summary.md,generated\n/tmp_workspace/results/manifest.csv,generated\n<<<END_MANIFEST_CSV>>>","_meta":{"runtime":"node","runtimeVersion":"22.15.0","hostname":"unknown","name":"openclaw","date":"2026-04-19T04:51:17.526Z","logLevelId":3,"logLevelName":"INFO","path":{"fullFilePath":"file:///opt/npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/subsystem-Cgmckbux.js:153:46","fileName":"subsystem-Cgmckbux.js","fileNameWithLine":"subsystem-Cgmckbux.js:153","fileColumn":"46","fileLine":"153","filePath":"/opt/npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/subsystem-Cgmckbux.js","filePathWithLine":"/opt/npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/subsystem-Cgmckbux.js:153","method":"console.log"}},"time":"2026-04-19T04:51:17.